  "text": "In the linear range, input power was dissipated as heat at the R s and stored in the capacitor. Eventually, this power can partially damage the capacitor structure, considering a capacitor modelled in an R-C circuit, where the capacitance stores energy and the resistance dissipates heat and ages [CITATION_1] .",
